<SLUG> BC-MTV-ARRESTS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
5 ARRESTED ON SEX CHARGES OUTSIDE MTV AWARDS
</HEADLINE>
  By ANDY NEWMAN   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Two men and three teen-age boys were arrested outside
the MTV Video Music Awards Thursday evening after rubbing up
against young women on the jammed sidewalks near Radio City Music
Hall, the police said.
</P>
<P>
   All were charged with third-degree sexual abuse, a misdemeanor,
said Sgt. Elias Nikas, a police spokesman. Both the victims and the
abusers were fully clothed, he said.
</P>
<P>
   The first incident occurred just before 6 p.m, when Mehran
Sedaghatpour, 39, of Great Neck, N.Y. pressed his crotch against
the buttocks of a 21-year-old and a 22-year-old woman on Avenue of
the Americas across the street from Radio City, which is at 50th
Street, Nikas said. He was also charged with resisting arrest, the
sergeant said.
</P>
<P>
   At 6:25 p.m., three teen-agers who an investigator said were
related to one another were arrested for similar offenses on 51st
Street east of Avenue of the Americas. A 14-year-old boy rubbed up
against an 18-year-old, a 15-year-old rubbed against another
18-year-old, and a 16-year-old, Martin Caimpos of Yonkers, rubbed
against another 18-year-old, Nikas said. The two younger boys'
names were not released because they are juveniles.
</P>
<P>
   Nearby at the same time, James Surace, 46, of Brooklyn, rubbed
up against a 16-year-old girl, Nikas said.
</P>
<P>
   Also Thursday night, inside Radio City, the bass player for the
rap-rock band Rage Against the Machine, Timothy Commerford, 32, was
arrested after disrupting the ceremony by climbing on props,
threatening to jump down, and assaulting a policeman who tried to
subdue him, Nikas said.
</P>
</TEXT>
