<P>
   CoxNet HEALTHY LIVING 0909 --COLLEGE WEIGHT GAIN -- Freshmen at
the nation's universities may still be unpacking in their dorm
rooms, but if they're anything like freshmen of years past, they're
already packing on the pounds. That's because among other college
rituals and traditions learned early on is the introduction of
college-style eating _ all-you-can-eat cafeterias, late-night pizza
deliveries, vending machine runs before class, fast food and cheap
libations. By the time they take their first semester finals, many
freshmen will have eaten their way to the dreaded ``Freshman 15.''
(Allmon, Waco Herald-Tribune)
</P>
<P>
   WITH: COLLEGE FIRST AID KIT -- It stands to reason that
semesters filled with sleepless nights, course-related stress and
abysmal eating habits will call for some first aid. (Jackson,
Austin American-Statesman)
</P>
<P>
   WITH: CREMATION -- Traditional funerals, with embalming,
caskets, religious services and ground burial in a family plot,
weren't really matters of choice. They were the rule.
</P>
<P>
   Not so today. More and more people are choosing to be cremated.
(Ardery, Austin American-Statesman)
