<P>
   CAMPAIGN-ROUNDUP (Undated) _ The Republican Party rides to the
aid of embattled GOP nominee George W. Bush with a blistering
televised attack on Democrat Al Gore that uses the Democrat's 1996
fund raising scandal to question his credibility in promising to
strengthen public education. On the campaign trail, Bush picks up
the endorsement of the National Fraternal Order of Police while
Gore touts a 10-year, $36 billion tax break for college tuition.
Democratic vice presidential candidate Joe Lieberman and Bush
campaign aides disagree over Bush's record in Texas on providing
health insurance to children. By STEWART M. POWELL.
