u e BC-WRESTLING-GRAPEVINE08     09-08 0465
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-WRESTLING-GRAPEVINE08-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Grapevine: News, notes from wrestling industry
 &HT;    By John Allen
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   The WWF completed an online auction on wwf.com in July that
raised over $50,000 for children's charities across the nation.
They continued the auction through August and will make a donation
to the Make-A-Wish Foundation.
</P>
<P>
   In July these were the top-selling items:
</P>
<P>
   Chris Jericho's autographed silver shirt $2,255
</P>
<P>
   Wrestlemania 2000 Autographed Banner $2,215
</P>
<P>
   HHH Autographed Outfit $2,055
</P>
<P>
   Wrestlemania 2000 WWF.com Ringskirt $2,030
</P>
<P>
   Chyna's Leather Outfit _ Autographed $2,005
</P>
<P>
   Steve Austin's autographed kneebrace $2,002
</P>
<P>
   Axxess Book signed by WWF Superstars $2,001
</P>
<P>
   Wrestlemania 2000 autographed tickets $1,750
</P>
<P>
   Chris Benoit's autographed tights $1,701
</P>
<P>
   Kat's autographed mud match bikini bottoms $1,557
</P>
<P>
   After months of speculation, the return of ``Stone Cold'' Steve
Austin appears to be set for Sept. 23 in Philadelphia for
``Unforgiven.''
</P>
<P>
   Austin made the claim during Thursday's ``Smackdown'' show that
he would be there to find out who tried to run him over with a car
last year. Austin, who has been out of action for nearly a year
after having neck surgery, will not be in the ring, but his return
should spark sales of the pay-per-view.
</P>
<P>
   His return would also come just a week before the World
Wrestling Federation's Monday night show, ``Raw is War,'' moves
from the USA Network to The Nashville Network.
</P>
<P>
   It appears as though the new deal between USA and Extreme
Championship Wrestling has hit a snag. ECW, which is looking for a
deal now that WWF has kicked them off TNN, would like a 6-8 p.m.
spot on Saturdays to keep its teenage fan base. USA would like to
move it to 11 p.m.-1 a.m. on the Saturday overnight, so ECW
over-the-top antics can remain uncut. Expect a deal to be worked
out soon because ECW needs a television deal to continue.
</P>
<P>
   More television news... It looks as though we might not see the
rat get her revenge in the ring. ``Survivor'' castaways Kelly and
Susan reportly have been contacted by WCW about being part of a
future
</P>
<P>
   pay-per-view. CBS/Viacom, which owns ``Survivor'' and just
purchased the rights to air WWF's ``Raw is War'' show would
probably fight such a deal unless the girls appear on WWF.
</P>
<P>
   Chyna's Playboy pictorial will hit newsstands on Sept. 29. She
will also release a workout video on Sept. 19. According to
wwf.com, ``Chyna Fitness isn't about having the biggest guns or the
tightest buns. Learn how to execute her 40-minute head-to-toe
circuit training program. Perfect for anybody who can't get to the
gym as much as they would like.''
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
