<P>
   PREGNANCY-RIGHTS (Undated) _ When does a pregnant woman _ or
even a potentially pregnant woman, given increasing medical
knowledge about reproductive health _ cross the line between
autonomy and obligation? In an age of reproductive freedom, when no
woman can be forced to carry a pregnancy to term, when if ever
should society intervene to protect the future interests of a child
a woman has chosen to bear? By Linda Greenhouse.
</P>
<P>
   MOYNIHAN-SCHOLARSHIP (Undatred) _ As he faces retirement from
the Senate, how does Daniel Patrick Moynihan stack up as a scholar?
