   &UR; OTHER CULTURE AND ENTERTAINMENT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   SCHWANN-MUSIC (Undated) _ The Schwann catalog, for more than 50
years the primary consumer listing of classical, jazz and pop
recordings, is replacing its quarterly Opus (classical) and
Spectrum (pop) catalogs with annual issues, supplemented by both a
constantly updated Web site and a monthly magazine, Schwann Inside.
The September debut issue of Schwann Inside was published last last
month, and includes listings, record reviews and performer
profiles. The Web site, www.schwann.com, is currently available
only to libaries, but will go public next month. Users will be
asked to pay an annual subscription fee of $99. By Allan Kozinn.
</P>
