   CUBA-OLYMPICS HAVANA _ With the Sydney Olympics set to begin in
September, Cuba is gearing up for another bout of sports-mania. The
tiny island nation has produced staggering numbers of medal winners
in past Olympics, and the games provide a rallying point for a
people shackled by a struggling economy and tight government
controls. We visit local ballfields and playgrounds to get a
grass-roots view of just what the Olympics and athletics mean to
everyday Cubans. (Williams, Cox News Service).
