   FBC-STOBART _ Chuck Stobart knows that most college football
coaches travel more than a circus act. But he was certain the
vagabond life was over when he joined Arizona's staff 14 years ago.
``I thought I was going to Arizona to retire,'' he said. ``We
re-did a house and six months later we moved.'' Stobart followed
head coach Larry Smith to Southern Cal, then went to Memphis to be
a head coach himself. He hooked on at Ohio State in 1994 and was
promoted to offensive coordinator this season. (Dayton Daily News)
