   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   HELEN-THOMAS (Washington) _ There's nobody at home at the White
House these days. Lame duckism is setting in. The White House,
often described by former occupants as the loneliest place in the
world, has certainly taken on that aura. The president is out
raising political contributions or traveling on the diplomatic
circuit. The first lady is busy in New York where she's running for
the Senate. Chelsea Clinton is dividing her time, spending some
with each parent. By HELEN THOMAS. (Already filed.)
