open criticism among many core Democrats about his centrist message
and running mate, Vice President Al Gore has moved swiftly to
consolidate his support among progressive Democrats and energize
once disaffected party activists, political analysts and Democratic
officials say. By James Dao.
</P>
<P>
   BUSH (Warrendale, Pa.) _ The new George Bush was on vivid
display Friday, talking to people in a cafeteria and recalling his
failed congressional race in 1976 when, he said, he didn't take
enough time to talk with voters. But all hasn't changed; the
Republican National Committee put out an ad on Friday that so far
is the harshest of the campaign, attacking Al Gore on campaign
finance. By Alison Mitchell.
