   PEST-INDUSTRY _ Complaints about termite inspections resound
nationwide. Accusations about various firms regularly failing to
perform adequate inspections _ even forging customer signatures on
reinspection tickets _ have cropped up in Florida, Alabama and
other states. As such charges of misbehavior persist the
pest-control industry battles a chronic credibility problem. Other
improprieties, regulators and consumers say, include applying
insufficient amounts of chemicals in termite treatments and
misleading customers on warranties. (Miller, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
