<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   PEST-GREEN _ The hot new weapon in the battle against America's
termites looks low-tech, resembling a footlong plastic screw.
Inside its hollow cylinder is placed a bait _ pieces of pine or
other wood. A dozen or more of these bait stations are planted in
the ground around a house. If termites start to nibble on the pine,
a chemical is put in the cavity, and the termites carry this poison
back to the colony. The death spiral begins. (Miller, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
