</P>
<P>
   COLLEGES
</P>
<P>
   FBC-FSU _ Florida State is 62-2 in the ACC since joining the
league in 1992. The original idea was that the Seminoles would help
elevate the league's level of football while improving its own
status in basketball. It could be argued that neither has come to
fruition. Today, the debate still rages that FSU joined the wrong
league. We'll get into it. (Barnhart, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   FBC-MIAMI-OHIO _ Geographically speaking, the road from
Nashville to Columbus does not run through Ypsilanti, Mich. But it
does on the map that plots the season for Miami and the RedHawks
better keep that in mind today as they face Eastern Michigan, a
detour ominously sandwiched between last Saturday's emotionally
draining season-opening win at Vanderbilt and next Saturday's
historic visit to Ohio State. (Dayton Daily News) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   FBC-STOBART _ Chuck Stobart knows that most college football
coaches travel more than a circus act. But he was certain the
vagabond life was over when he joined Arizona's staff 14 years ago.
``I thought I was going to Arizona to retire,'' he said. ``We
re-did a house and six months later we moved.'' Stobart followed
head coach Larry Smith to Southern Cal, then went to Memphis to be
a head coach himself. He hooked on at Ohio State in 1994 and was
promoted to offensive coordinator this season. (Dayton Daily News)
MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   FBC-AGGIES _ The Texas A&AMP;M Aggies play their second college
football game against Wyoming. 6 p.m. (CST) Saturday. (Riggs,
Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
