</P>
<P>
   Beginning at 9 p.m. today and continuing at 9 p.m. Monday,
Tuesday and Wednesday, local PBS stations will air ``On Our Own
Terms: Moyers on Dying.'' This PBS series by Bill and Judith
Davidson Moyers examines the options available for the terminally
ill. The series will be repeated at various times throughout the
week. Each part focuses on different topics.
</P>
<P>
   _ Tonight: ``Living with Dying'' focuses on the choices faced by
the terminally ill and their families.
</P>
<P>
   _ Monday: ``A Different Kind of Care'' looks Mount Sinai
Hospital in New York City, where the focus is making death as
comfortable a transition as possible.
</P>
<P>
   _ Tuesday: ``A Death of One's Own'' looks at the steps people
take in the decision of when to suspend debilitating treatments.
</P>
<P>
