<P>
   MEXICO-FIREFIGHTERS (Kerrville, Texas) _ With blazes
overpowering American firefighters in several western and southern
states this summer, a specially trained corps of Mexicans is
helping on the fire line. Organized by the National Park Service in
1990, the crew has grown and is being recognized for its hot,
dangerous work. By ZEKE MacCORMACK. (Already filed.)
