<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Dress down backlash; it's all about better dressing
 &HT;    Eds: Embargoed for Sunday, Sept. 10.
 &HT;    By A. Scott Walton
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   If it's the back-slashers who first led us into ultra-casual
workwear, it's only fitting that those I.T. professionals are
leading the way back to more polished dressing.
</P>
<P>
   Designers everywhere have tuned into the new affluence,
modernity and versatility of the dot-com culture and produced an
incredibly diverse array of styles that are at once luxurious,
sexy, assertive and wearable. Through innovation, they've succeeded
in making traditional fabrics like tweed lighter and more pliable;
they've luxed up sportswear by rendering it in suedes and leathers,
and they've reinterpreted suits in softer, curvier silhouettes.
</P>
<P>
   The Atlanta dot-commers we asked to model the latest fall styles
were ideally suited to the task. They arrived for the photo shoot
in cuff-linked shirts, sport coats, skirted suits and scarf-tied
blouse _ cues they're already part of the backlash against the
corporate casual culture. More importantly, they were comfortable
wearing the clothes we selected.
</P>
<P>
   Dressing up feels right right now.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Aimee Uy, Web developer, eTour.com
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Fashion do: ``Keep it simple and you can't go wrong.''
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Fashion don't: ``Don't wear something just because it's
fashionable; make sure you're comfortable in it or else you won't
make much of a statement.''
</P>
<P>
   Suede pants ($318) by Josephine Loka, tweed shell ($245) by
Joseph, from Saks Fifth Avenue. Python shoes ($350) by Reed Evins,
from Neiman Marcus.
</P>
<P>
   Eric Grossman, CEO,
</P>
<P>
   SimplyHealth.
</P>
<P>
   com
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Fashion do: ``Get a Mont Blanc pen, make sure your shoe soles
aren't worn out and wear pressed clothing.''
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Fashion don't: Don't wear socks that are too short, don't wear
cologne at the office and don't wear your Palm Pilot or cell phone
on your belt.''
</P>
<P>
   Blazer ($995), shirt ($165) and pants ($325) by Armani
Collezioni, from Neiman Marcus. Shoes ($100) from Kenneth Cole at
North Georgia Premium Outlets.
</P>
<P>
   Jennifer McCollum, press director, EzGov
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Fashion do: ``Wear clean, classy lines, spiced up with funky
accessories like fun shoes or funky retro glasses with colorful
rims.''
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Fashion don't: ``Avoid the blue suit, pantyhose and pearls
combination at all costs.''
</P>
<P>
   Embroidered skirt ($295) and jacket ($528) by Dries Van Noten,
from Jeffrey Atlanta. Pumps ($280) by Giorgio Armani, from Bob
Ellis Shoes.
</P>
<P>
   Hal Logan, CEO/president, Manheim Interactive
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Fashion do: ``Make sure the colors you wear complement each
other, your skin tone and the season.''
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Fashion don't: ``For me, it's trying to combine stripes and
plaids in the same outfit. Just doesn't work for me.''
</P>
<P>
   Shirt jacket ($550), undershirt ($50) and slacks ($195) by
Bernard Zins, from Sebastian's Closet.
</P>
<P>
   Porter Payne, vice president, WebMD
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Fashion do: ``Make sure your shoes, belt and socks all
match.''
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Fashion don't: ``Never wear a shirt that's untucked.''
</P>
<P>
   Mock T-shirt ($95), shirt jacket ($550) and slacks ($325) by
Bernard Zins, from Sebastian's Closet. Shoes ($100) from the
Kenneth Cole at North Georgia Premium Outlets.
</P>
<P>
   Toni Moceri, Executive VP, webdiamonds.
</P>
<P>
   com
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Fashion do: ``Drink lots of water, and be from the Midwest;
people from there age slower.''
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Fashion don't: ``Never get too much sun; it has helped me.''
</P>
<P>
   Tweed jacket ($745) and skirt ($345) by Moschino, from Saks
Fifth Avenue. Pumps ($155) by Via Spiga, from Rich's.
</P>
<P>
   Pamela Jackson, executive assistant, WebMD
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Fashion do: ``If you're wearing shoes and hose, make sure they
blend together.''
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Fashion don't: ``I don't like outfits that are the same color
from head to toe. Be more creative.''
</P>
<P>
   Jacket ($1,090), skirt ($380) and blouse ($475) by Calvin Klein,
from Neiman Marcus. Pumps ($110) by BCBG, from Rich's.
</P>
<P>
   Jacqueline Crawley, program manager, iXL
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Fashion do: ``I always wear earth tones because I can easily
mix and match them with colors.''
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Fashion don't: ``I hate when I see chipped nail polish; that
irks me.''
</P>
<P>
   Leather coat ($499) by Guess, silk blouse ($208) and pants
($218) by Tahari, pumps ($110) by BCBG, all from Rich's.
</P>
<P>
   SECOND SHOT
</P>
<P>
   Christi Bennett, business manager, active.com
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Fashion do: ``Buy fun shoes first, and then the outfit.''
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Fashion don't: ``Don't chomp your gum, it makes you look
ugly.''
</P>
<P>
   Mink-trimmed camel shell ($229) and skirt ($179) by Tempesta,
