r l BC-GOTTAHAVE10-COX     09-08 0572
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-GOTTAHAVE10-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Five must haves for the Fall season
 &HT;    Eds: Emabargoed for Sunday, Sept. 10.
 &HT;    By Marylin Johnson
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QR;  Something in leather
</P>
<P>
   Sleek and sophisticated, it's the fabric of the season. Look for
it in jeans, coats, skirts and shirts. Black is a runaway favorite,
but also look for red, camel and brown pieces. Our choice: Anne
Klein's black leather jacket with zip-front ($298). Also shown:
Anne Klein black leather pants ($298) and Via Spiga's black leather
pumps ($155). All at Rich's.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  A chunky sweater
</P>
<P>
   Textured sweaters are tops this fall. But that doesn't mean
bulky. Larger-gauze stitches, heavy-ply yarns and funnel necks help
create this cool look for cool days. Our choice: Sleeveless green
sweater from Classiques Entier ($118). At Nordstrom.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Something in gold
</P>
<P>
   The Midas look counts in bold accessories. But if you don't want
to take it to the extreme, opt for simplicity and rush to the
forefront of fashion. Our choices: Bonnie J hoop earrings ($10);
gold bangles from Jennifer Moore (a box of five, $14.99); a shiny
gold belt with studs ($26). All at Macy's.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  The bowling bag
</P>
<P>
   You will strike the right fashion note carrying this large bag,
in which a cosmetics case, billfold and all your daily necessities
will neatly fit. This silhouette comes in smooth leathers as well
as fabrics and suedes. Our choice: Black/tan leather bowling bag
from Miu Miu ($410). At Neiman Marcus.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  A pretty blouse
</P>
<P>
   It's the logical partner for the new ladylike suits and the
perfect expression of this year's softened femininity. Look for
blouses in prints and solids, in silks, chiffons and blends. Our
choice: I.N.C.'s wine-red blouse with necktie ($59). At Macy's.
</P>
<P>
   Five gotta haves for him
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Something in leather
</P>
<P>
   For a luxurious look and feel, the leather jacket is a must.
Pair it with jeans, flannels, tweeds, even a matching pair of
leather trousers. Our choices: Alfani's black leather blazer
($395). Also shown, Alfani's black leather trousers ($295). Both at
Rich's. Black leather slip-ons from Halogen ($180). At Nordstrom.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  A luxurious T-shirt
</P>
<P>
   Cotton just doesn't do it this year. Opt instead for a shirt in
cashmere, silk or merino wool and wear it under blazers or a suit.
Our choice: Perry Ellis' silk-blend T in a textured cream color
($65). At Rich's.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  French-cuff shirt
</P>
<P>
   When a shirt is required for business, think about the
dressed-up look of a French-cuff dress shirt with cuff links. It's
a bit more formal look than a regular cuffed shirt and decidedly
French dressing. Our choice: Giorgio Armani's blue shirt ($185),
John Hardy silver cuff links ($150) and Etro dot tie ($95). All at
Saks Fifth Avenue.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  A techno watch
</P>
<P>
   If you have time on your hands, go for the look of a sports
watch. It's cool and ultra-sleek, especially with a techno band.
Our choice: Techno Marine chronograph watch with a black high-tech
band and yellow face ($300). At Neiman Marcus.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Pair of color wash jeans
</P>
<P>
   The perennial blue denims have faded a bit from the spotlight.
Go for a pair in a black, gray or olive color. Torn, patched and
stamped jeans are also in the jean pool. Our choice: Black wash
jeans from Phat Farm ($78). At Macy's.
</P>
<P>
   Marylin Johnson writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
