and NY-CUBA-CASTRO move inside; adds BUSH-DEBATES.) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Here are the stories New York Times editors are planning for
Page 1, Saturday, Sept. 9. The night supervisor for The New York
Times News Service is Pat Ryan; phone: 888-346-9867 or
212-556-1927; e-mail: patryan(at)nytimes.com.
</P>
<P>
   TOP
</P>
<P>
   Lead story:
</P>
<P>
   U.N.-MILLENNIUM-SUMMIT (United Nations) _ Three days of
brainstorming by the leaders of virtually all the world's nations
ends with a brave attempt to agree on a set of goals for the next
millennium,and common values by which to govern. It was not easy,
but more than 150 leaders and few stand-ins tried to mesh the
demands for universal democracy, the rule of law and human rights,
including the equality of women with demands by poor nations for
better balance in the world's economy and more benefits from the
rise of globalization. By Barbara Crossette. (We plan to move the
story by 9 p.m. ET in ``i'' news file.) 1,600 words.
</P>
