effort to impose his own schedule of presidential debates, and his
campaign says it is prepared to sit down with aides to Vice
President Al Gore to work out an agreement for debating under the
auspices of a bipartisan commission. By Peter Marks. (Scheduled to
move by 9 p.m. ET in ``p'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   Story runs under 3-column photo.
</P>
<P>
   Off-lead story:
</P>
<P>
   NY-BRICK-ATTACK (New York) _ A look at the lives of the five
