<HEADLINE>
OLYMPIC CAPSULE: SOFTBALL  
 (FOR RELEASE MONDAY, SEPT. 11) 
</HEADLINE>
   By BILL PENNINGTON   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   Four years ago in Atlanta, the U.S. women's softball team, with
one defeat in the previous 10 years of international competition,
was supposed to win the Olympic gold medal in a walkover. Then the
Australians defeated the United States, 2-1, in 10 innings of an
early round game. Then it was up to the Chinese women to press the
Americans in the gold-medal game. The Americans narrowly avoided an
upset when America's fiery infielder Dot Richardson hit a dramatic
game-ending home run.
</P>
<P>
   During these Olympics, the Americans are still heavily favored _
most think this year's team has more power hitters _ but the
Australians and Chinese have improved, too. They are more
experienced, with each team having farmed out its best players to
foreign professional softball leagues between Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
   THE SETUP
</P>
<P>
   Eight teams play a round-robin tournament, with the top four
teams advancing to the semifinals followed by the gold-medal game.
</P>
<P>
   THE SCORING
</P>
<P>
   It's nine players a side, no extra outfielder. A game is usually
seven innings, but if the score is still tied after nine innings,
each team starts its turn at bat with a runner at second base.
</P>
<P>
   THE STRATEGY
</P>
<P>
   It's a pitcher's game even if the hitters wield aluminum bats.
Bunting is common, as is the attempt to chop down on a pitch,
hitting a high-bouncing ground ball that either leads to an infield
hit or bounces over the infield. Games that end 1-0 and 2-1 are
routine.
</P>
<P>
   Home runs are rare, but the Americans have developed some pull
hitters who can go deep, most notably Crystl Bustos and Jen
Brundage.
</P>
<P>
   THE NAMES
</P>
<P>
   Lisa Fernandez, the top U.S. pitcher who also hit .348 in the
Atlanta Summer Games, is back. Michele Smith is the team's other
premier pitcher.
</P>
<P>
   Richardson, who will turn 39 on Sept. 22, is the oldest member
of the U.S. team. Bustos is a newcomer to the Olympic team, but
some believe she will eventually be the best women's softball
hitter in history.
</P>
<P>
   The Australians are led by pitcher Tanya Harding _ not that
Tonya Harding _ who did not allow an earned run in 222/3 innings of
work during the Atlanta Games and defeated the Americans.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
