<HEADLINE>
BRUINS DO HAVE A CHALLENGE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BILLY WITZ  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &LR; LOS ANGELES _ There will be thousands of fans dressed in red,
enough motor homes parked outside the Rose Bowl to make it look
like a trailer park, and the visiting team lining up in white
uniforms and red helmets.
</P>
<P>
   Maybe UCLA can convince itself that it's playing Alabama again.
</P>
<P>
   That figures to be the biggest challenge for the Bruins,
convincing themselves that this afternoon's hole in the middle of
their schedule _ Fresno State, surrounded by games against then-No.
3 Alabama and current No. 3 Michigan _ is worth getting excited
about.
</P>
<P>
   To that end, UCLA coach Bob Toledo stepped up the intensity in
practice on Wednesday with his coaches barking orders and a sense
of urgency pervading drills. He's even broached a subject with his
players that would have seemed ridiculous a week ago _ playing for
a national championship.
</P>
<P>
   ``They realize what's at stake,'' Toledo said. ``I asked them,
`If you're going to pick the BCS now, who would you pick, Alabama
or UCLA?' We've done some nice things. For us to stub our toe would
be a real tragedy.''
</P>
<P>
   While the 16th-ranked Bruins are 14-point favorites over Fresno
State, Toledo said it is important just to win, not score a big
victory. However, if the win over Alabama proved that the Bruins
have top-10 caliber talent, this game should be a test of whether
they have national-caliber character.
</P>
<P>
   If the Bruins can run the ball down the throat of Alabama, why
can't they do it to Fresno State? If the Bruins can smother
Alabama's offense, why can't they do it to the Bulldogs?
</P>
<P>
   There will be no letdown, assured center Troy Danoff.
</P>
<P>
   ``There's no reason for it,'' said Danoff, who with guards Brian
Polak and Oscar Cabrera, tackles Bryce Bohlander and Mike Saffer,
and tight ends Gabe Crecion, Mike Seidman and Bryan Fletcher
dominated Alabama's front seven.
</P>
<P>
   ``In football, you only play 11 games _ 12 if you get the
opportunity to go to a bowl game _ so it's not too hard o,{
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-09-08-00 2316EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
