that has transformed itself from a conventional bank into a giant
back office for the global investment industry. His first goal
clear: As markets and technology systems become more
interconnected, his company, long marked by divisiveness, must
undergo a cultural makeover. Spina at the Bank of England building
in London. (Carlos Lopez-Barillas/The New York Times)
